column11: LOTRLandmark
Leave Bag End at full dark. Go around (W) end, jump hedge. After 1 Mile Go through gate into a lane. Head west.

At 2 miles: Left lane, followed hedgerows south.
At the 3rd mile we cross The Water on a plank bridge
Saw the Brandywine Bridge coming up in half a mile
Crossed The Great Road from the Brandywine Bridge. Enter Tookland.
Came to the foot of the first slopes of the Green Hill Country
Look back at lights of Hobbiton from first slopes of the Green Hill Country.
Hobbiton hidden as slopes rise and fall. Birches in the distance ahead
Pass a few birches and notice there's a treeline
Stop in a birch grove. Eat a frugal supper.
Set off into the deep of the birch grove. The other side nowhere in sight
Reached the end of the grove. Arrived at Stock Road.
Begin to sing. Walk through a deeply cloven track between tall trees.
Climb a steep slope. Pippins yawns (nearly midnight)
Camp - In a firwood just over top of the hill. Sleep by a large tree. Fox sees us.
Eat at campsite. Water from a stream at the foot of the hill. A little fall where the water fell a few feet over an outcrop of grey stone.  After 10:00 a.m. when we leave.
Road rolls up and down. It looks to do so for what looks to be miles and miles
We walk up and down more rolling hills, they go on forever
Yet more hills... is this life now?
More hills for what seems like miles
We continue to walk past hills, we're now enjoying the pastures
If we see one more hill....
The hills are our family now.

Road zig-zigs to top of a steep bank and goes down for the last time. Can see across Woody End to the River. **WE STOP TO REST, EAT, and REST more! Sun was "beginning to get low" as they went down the hill.
We continue on to walk on a curvy road
The road ahead looks to turn and head onward, straight
Road ahead runs fairly straight and level. Behind them it curves slightly. BLACK RIDER. Sam and Pippin hide in a hollow. Frodo behind tree by road
We hid from the BLACK RIDER and conitnued onward.
Keep a stone's throw left of the road...slower going.
Remained on the left of the road

Road splits. Road to Stock bends left and goes down into the lowlands. They take a lane which branches to the right, winding through a wood of ancient Oaks. 'Sun down and evening coming on'. Quite close to the road-meeting they creep inside a huge tree. Eat and rest.
Go on in twilight. Begin to sing.
Continued Singing
"And NOW to bed!"  Pippin says, when BLACK RIDER is heard again. ELVES arrive, RIDER leaves, and Frodo & Co. continue with Elves.
Wood more dense, and lane went lower, running in a fold of hills, with hazel on the slopes alongside. Pippin quickly becomes sleepy.
Turn right off the path on 'a green ride' through thickets.
Camp - Woody End. A green floor in the wood, roofed by boughs of trees. To the east a steep shoulder falls, and they can overlook the river valley. The lights of the village of Woodhall seen below.
Sleep late. Frodo decides to cut SE to Buckleberry Ferry. Scramble down hill into the thick trees below. It begins to cloud up.
A deep-banked stream below the hill cuts across their path. Looking back, they see a Black Rider on the hillcrest where they had camped. They force through the bushes alongside the stream.
Pippin realizes it is the Stock-brook. The banks are low enough now for them to cross. The land on its south bank is wet and reedy.
They reach a belt of trees, mostly oaks with a few elms and ash. Drops of rain fall.
Head south through the belt of trees.
Pippin realizes they've turned too far south as they are still in the trees.
Head north through the belt of trees
Still in the trees, they stop for lunch. Their singing is cut by the cry of a Black Rider, and they leave.
Wood ends. The land steadily becomes more tame. Sun is shining brightly.
Reach area of the Marish with fields, meadows, hedges, gates, and drainage dikes.
Crossing a field and snuck through a gate
Followed a drainage dike past some hedges
Made their way to the edge of the Marish with fields
Edges of fields worked by Farmer Maggot.
After a turnip field there is a stout gate to a rutted lane, edged by hedges.
Farmer Maggot's house and buildings: brick with thatched roofs, surrounded by a high wall cut by a wooden gate from the lane. Eat. (full dark when they leave).
Leave Maggot's house and make way toward Buckleberry Ferry
Travelled Maggot's lane down a ways, a wagon approached in the distance
Farmer Maggot's lane meets the Causeway to Buckleberry Ferry. Ride in wagon.
Continued on the Wagon ride.
The wagon ride was quite long.
Dozed a bit in the wagon, but a thought of the Black Rider shook them awake
The land began getting soggy all around, a bog was approaching
Boggy land all around. Foggy. Merry meets them at the Ferry landing. As they reach the other side of the river, they can see a Black Rider on the west shore.
Taking the main road north from the Ferry, Buck Hill is on the left and Buckleberry on the right. They take a lane to the right, and climb up and down into the country.
Crickhollow - spend the night. "A Conspiracy Unmasked".
Leave Crickhollow soon after 6:00 a.m. Foggy. Ride ponies slowly.
Ponies approach a runnel under a hedge, up ahead
Enter tunnel under Hedge to reach The Old Forest. Path disappears
Wandering through the Old Forest, trying to keep straight
Trusting that they're crossing the Old Forest well
The Bonfire Glade - clear path beyond. Sunny, but not yet in clearing
On path in the Forest. Path climbs gently.
The gentle climb looks to continue for miles
The gentle climb looks to continue for miles
The gentle climb looks to continue for miles
Stubbed pinky toe --- let's keep on the gentle climb, slowly
The gentle climb looks to continue for miles
The gentle climb looks to continue for miles
Thank goodness for the gentle climb, the pinky toe recovers
The gentle climb looks to continue for miles
The gentle climb looks to continue for miles
Top of knoll in Forest! Hazy. Surrounded by Trees. Eat, rest
Headed down the knoll, path looks to be veering
Path veers SE. Company leaves path and tries to turn north.
Cross series of deep folds running SE. Keep turning east. Lose direction.
The deep folds continue and seemigly getting deeper and steeper
Enter fold too deep to leave. Follow it SE to Withywindle
Can't go back, continue on the Withywindle
Seemingly continuing in the right direction
Merry finds path along bank of the River. Follow it east through wetlands.
The path continues onward, slogging through the wetlands
Stop by Old Man Willow to rest. Rescued by Tom Bombadil.
Travel with Tom Bombadil
Reach Tom Bombadil's house. Stars are out.
Rainy. Spend the day at Tom Bombadil's house.
Leave Tom Bombadil's house and climb zig-zag path to brow of hill on west side of Barrow-downs
On ponies go up steep slopes and down long limbs.
No trees or water.
The land looks stark and unwelcoming
There is thirst, but supplies must be conserved
Ponies earn their keep trekking through more slopes and limbs
The direction seems true, but the distance long
The slopes continued on for miles
They travelled in silence hoping they had lost the evil creatures that chased them
They noticed the direction looked off, with the sky how it was
Turn more east than they intend and enter the Barrow-downs, a place of great dread: inhabited by evil Barrow-wights from Angmar
Dreading the trek through the barrow-downs they press forward
The Barrows seem to go on forever
The Barrows seem to go on forever
The Barrows seem to go on forever
The Barrows seem to go on forever
Some fatigue setting in, getting tired, and hungry
See hills in the distance, will need to sleep soon
A hollow looks to be atop a hill nearby, head in that direction
Midday. Stop in a hollow atop a hill. Eat and fall asleep. Wake in fog, sun sinking.
The fog is thick and there is little visibility
Need to head the correct way, north.
Try to head north, but lose their way and become separated. Captured by Wights.
Frodo sings, Tom rescues and recalls ponies. Tom leads.
Following Tom through the unknown
Realizing how far Bree is from us
Missing a little bit of home; we'll be back soon enough
Tom angles us up headed north
Ride north through a gap.
Moving northward
All this land used to beling to the North Kingdom of Arnor
The land all around is better than it was in the barrows
Getting Hungry
Reach dike and hedge. Former boundary of Cardolan, part of the North Kingdom of Arnor.
Passing through the former boundary of Cardolan
We continue North, but we should be heading East
There is no road beneath us, how is Tom travelling?
Continued nothing
Walked over the crest of a hill, a few miles ahead is the Great East Road
Started heading down the hill, the Great East Road disappears beyond the horizon
Pass a small brook
The trees around you thin out a bit
The land flattens out and the Great East Road is up ahead
Return to Great East Road. Tom departs. Strider sees them, but hides.
Follow the Road up aways, a town in the distance
Looks like Bree is up ahead, one more mile and we can rest
Reach Bree. Stay at The Prancing Pony. Meet Strider. Ponies stolen during night
Leave Bree on East Road
Will be at least five miles on the East Road before heading North again
Not passing many people, but no sight of Black Riders either
The East Road looks long and quiet
Leave road and head north into Chetwood. No living things all day.
Camp in Chetwood, east of Archet.
Head east. Ground dropping slowly. Quiet and peaceful.
Camp in eastern Chetwood.
Come out of the Chetwood.
